result.execSummary:
The defendant Dawn M. Anderson was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Forgery-Uttering [Modifiers: Party to a Crime], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.38(2).
  • Fraud Against Financial Institution (Value does not Exceed $500), a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.82(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant's Motion for Release Pending Appeal.

Defendant appeared with counsel Matt Prior.  DA Gerald Fox appears for the State.  There are no corrections/changes to the PSI by either counsel.  DA recommends the following:  14CF191, Count 2 - 5-year bifurcated sentence of 2 years initial confinement and 3 years extended supervision; 14CF191, Count 3, 14CF197, Count 2, and 14CM262, Count 1 recommends consecutive probation terms.  Attorney prior recommends 3 years probation on each with no prison.  Defendant speaks.  State requests restitution on each case as follows:  14CF191 - $85.00 to CCU; 14CM262 - $66.82 to Oriental Kitchen; 14CF197 - $125.00 to Cozy Corner, $850.38 to Burnstads, $177.94 to Cataract Mart, $57.15 to Falls Cafe a total of $1210.47 in that case.  Court ordered sentences in following cases:  14CF191, Count 2 - 6 year bifurcated sentence of 3 years initial incarceration and 3 years extended supervision and is eligible for Substance Abuse Program.  14CF191, Count 3 & 14CM262, Count 1 - Sentence withheld and placed on 2 years probation consecutive to 14CF191, Count 2.  14CF197, Count 2 - Sentence withheld and placed on 3 years probation concurrent to probation terms on 14CF191 and 14CM262 but consecutive to prison sentence.  Conditions of extended supervision and probation are:  Must comply with any recommended treatment/counseling per agent's recommendations.  Defendant must submit to random urinalysis by probation agent or any law enforcement officer.  Not allowed to write or issue any checks.  Must set up a payment plan with agent to pay on restitution.  Must pay the costs of the action and all restitution as requested by DA.  Must submit a DNA sample and pay the surcharge.  Credit for 3 days jail on 14CF191.  Defendant was remanded to Jackson County Jail.
